From: fupan li <fupan.li@windriver.com>
Date: Sun, 17 Mar 2013 17:50:03 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] fix CPU_HOTPLUG cuasing kernel call trace

commit 85b97637bb40a9f486459dd254598759af9c3d50 added the following codes:
        if (cpu == smp_processor_id()) {
                cmci_rediscover_work_func(NULL);
into cmci_rediscover() function, which would be called from preemptible
context and causes kernel call trace. For more information about this bug,
and fix, please refer to https://patchwork.kernel.org/patch/2169371/

Signed-off-by: Thomas Gleixner <tglx@linutronix.de>
Signed-off-by: fupan li <fupan.li@windriver.com>
---
 arch/x86/kernel/cpu/mcheck/mce_intel.c |    4 +++-
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/x86/kernel/cpu/mcheck/mce_intel.c b/arch/x86/kernel/cpu/mcheck/mce_intel.c
index 915457b..cd08793 100644
--- a/arch/x86/kernel/cpu/mcheck/mce_intel.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kernel/cpu/mcheck/mce_intel.c
@@ -205,10 +205,12 @@ void cmci_rediscover(int dying)
 		if (cpu == dying)
 			continue;
 
-		if (cpu == smp_processor_id()) {
+		if (cpu == get_cpu()) {
 			cmci_rediscover_work_func(NULL);
+			put_cpu();
 			continue;
 		}
+		put_cpu();
 
 		work_on_cpu(cpu, cmci_rediscover_work_func, NULL);
 	}
